						<summary>

						<p>An image in the ruined temple called Bairavuni Tippa on the river bank.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Sādhāraṇa, Bhādrapada ba. 11, Wednesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>Incomplete. It mentions certain individuals like Vaḍḍipāti-Siṁggarāju, his wife Akkasāni and their sons Timmarāju and Yaṟṟamarāju. It also mentions that Kotta bellēkōṭa is situated in Yeruva. In characters of 14th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
